Body: Description: I am auditing site permissions and see that there are multiple sharePoint online sites that are listed in SharePoint online which do not appear in the Resource Audit of the enterprise auditor. I am running version 11.6 of the application.

I would request a copy of a debug log from the scan either SPAA or SPSEEK.

See if any errors or warnings correspond with the missing sites.

Confirm the scans are going deep enough if they are subsites.

client called in

took control of ticket

 

zoom meeting

The customer called in and mentioned that the SEEK System scan completed with an error. He uploaded a screenshot of the error with the error message to the ticket.

 

I advised the customer to run the SPAA System Scan and the Bulk Import.

I advised him to upload the log to the ticket once the scan is completed.

Invitation updated. Attendees: Joshua Sexton, Tay Caliguiri
Invitation updated. Attendees: Joshua Sexton, Tay Caliguiri, Chan Pin

What We've Learned Updated: SPSEEK scan wasn't suffcient because it was scoped for a particular site

removed scoping limitation
dropped all SP data and scanned fresh with just the SPSEEK job (SPAA disabled)

now the sites are showing properly in the AIC
requested the client extend the scan depth from 4 to full

client still having issue with a few user AD accounts not appearing consistently accross AD and entra ID reports

needs a new ticket
Next Steps Updated: creating ticket for AD user account issue
